---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="About"
  description="What Intent Alpha is, how it works, and what it isn't."
>
  <h1>About</h1>
  <p>
    <strong>Intent Alpha</strong> reads the public job postings of leading technology
    companies and infers what they are building next. Each article is an explicit hypothesis
    grounded in the hiring signals it rests on.
  </p>

  <h2>How it works</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>We pull job postings from public sources: Greenhouse, Lever, and Workday.</li>
    <li>We track changes over time — what roles appear, disappear, and cluster.</li>
    <li>From those patterns we form a hypothesis about the company's direction.</li>
    <li>Each hypothesis ships with a confidence label and an explicit horizon.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>What this is not</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Not investment advice.</li>
    <li>Not insider information &mdash; everything is sourced from public listings.</li>
    <li>Not a guarantee &mdash; hypotheses are falsifiable by design.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Sources</h2>
  <p>
    Job postings are read from publicly accessible endpoints provided by the applicant
    tracking systems each company uses. We respect <code>robots.txt</code> and stated terms.
  </p>
</Layout>
